The paper focuses on the application of deep convolutional neural networks to computer-aided detection problems in medical imaging, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also explores different CNN architectures and evaluates the influence of dataset characteristics, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image recognition and classification, which are relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses transfer learning, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning.
